<paragraph id="8BE5FB4F101FFFAAFF64F98F79D853D5" blockId="8.[136,1452,914,1984]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFF64F98F79475269" bold="true" box="[189,265,1634,1660]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Notes:</emphasis>
Our isolate 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A101FFFAAFE43F98F7A4F5269" box="[410,513,1634,1660]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">KUMCC</collectionCode>
21-0468 fits with the characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFC16F98E7CFE5269" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" baseAuthorityName="Balsamo-Crivelli" box="[975,1200,1634,1660]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFC16F98E7CFE5269" box="[975,1200,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Beauveria bassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having an asexual morph producing globose to subglobose, catenated conidia, aseptate, hyaline, with globose to flask-shaped phialides; conidiogenous cells normally cluster on the terminals of branched hypha (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFC6EF9477C9252D1" author="Paul Vuillemin, M." box="[951,1244,1706,1732]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="34 - 40" refId="ref13613" refString="Paul Vuillemin, M. (1912) Beauveria, nouveau genre de Verticilliacees. Bulletin de la societe botanique de france 59: 34 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00378941.1912.10832379" type="journal article" year="1912">
Paul Vuillemin 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFBBCF9467CD252D1" box="[1125,1180,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
1912
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFB3FF9477DEE52D1" author="Chen, M. J. &amp; Huang, B. &amp; Li, Z. Z. &amp; Spatafora, J. W." box="[1254,1440,1706,1732]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="301 - 308" refId="ref9186" refString="Chen, M. J., Huang, B., Li, Z. Z., Spatafora, J. W. (2013) Morphological and genetic characterisation of Beauveria sinensis sp. nov. from China. Mycotaxon 124: 301 - 308. https: // doi. org / 10.5248 / 124.301" type="journal article" year="2013">
Chen 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFAFEF9467D1052D1" box="[1319,1374,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). The clade 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFF22F922793352FD" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" baseAuthorityName="Balsamo-Crivelli" box="[251,381,1742,1768]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFF22F922793352FD" box="[251,381,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">B. bassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was analysed in detail by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE101FFFAAFD46F9237BEA52FD" author="Khonsanit, A. &amp; Thanakitpipattana, D. &amp; Noisripoom, W. &amp; Chaitika, T. &amp; Kobmoo, N." box="[671,932,1742,1768]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="291 - 315" refId="ref12427" refString="Khonsanit, A., Luangsa-ard, J. J., Thanakitpipattana, D., Noisripoom, W., Chaitika, T. &amp; Kobmoo, N. (2020) Cryptic diversity of the genus Beauveria with a new species from Thailand. Mycological Progress 19: 291 - 315. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 020 - 01557 - 9" type="journal article" year="2020">
Khonsanit 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFCC0F9227B1E52FD" box="[793,848,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
. The 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A101FFFAAFC06F9237C4752FD" box="[991,1033,1742,1768]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">ITS</collectionCode>
BLASTn results of our isolate highly overlapped with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFE93F91E7A655319" authorityName="Vuillemin" authorityYear="1912" baseAuthorityName="Balsamo-Crivelli" box="[330,555,1778,1804]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFE93F91E7A655319" box="[330,555,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Beauveria bassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strains 
<accessionNumber id="940966AC101FFFAAFD5EF91F7B465319" box="[647,776,1778,1804]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/BCC34332" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A101FFFAAFD5EF91F7A8E5319" box="[647,704,1778,1804]" country="Thailand" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/e7v8-j84z" name="BIOTEC Culture Collection" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" type="Living organism collection (e.g., culture collection, seedbank)">BCC</collectionCode>
34332
</accessionNumber>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A101FFFAAFCCCF91F7B225319" box="[789,876,1778,1804]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" name="U.S. Plant, Soil and Nutrition Laboratory, USDA/ARS" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" type="Herbarium">ARSEF</collectionCode>
751 and 
<accessionNumber id="940966AC101FFFAAFC05F91F7C125319" box="[988,1116,1778,1804]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/BBC12907" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">BBC12907</accessionNumber>
, while 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFB6AF91F7CA65319" box="[1203,1256,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">rpb1</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFB21F91F7D635319" box="[1272,1325,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">rpb2</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFAB0F91F7DE55319" box="[1385,1451,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">tef1-α</emphasis>
show high matches to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFE5FF8FA7AE65325" authority="ARSEF 1040" authorityName="ARSEF" authorityYear="1040" box="[390,680,1814,1840]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFE5FF8FA7A445325" box="[390,522,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">B. bassiana</emphasis>
ARSEF 1040
</taxonomicName>
(&gt;99%). In addition, Bloc gene region showed 100% (1486/1492, 1 gap) similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFE8BF8D679985341" authorityName="ARSEF" authorityYear="1040" box="[338,470,1850,1876]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFE8BF8D679985341" box="[338,470,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">B. bassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A101FFFAAFE3DF8D77A735341" box="[484,573,1850,1876]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14687" name="U.S. Plant, Soil and Nutrition Laboratory, USDA/ARS" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" type="Herbarium">ARSEF</collectionCode>
4934), and our tree topology of the 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A101FFFAAFC0EF8D67C4E5340" box="[983,1024,1851,1877]" country="France" name="Musee de Lectoure" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">ML</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A101FFFAAFBE1F8D67C1A5340" box="[1080,1108,1851,1877]" country="Italy" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13366" name="Istituto Ortobotanico" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" type="Herbarium">BI</collectionCode>
analyses also shows 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A101FFFAAFA9CF8D77DE25341" box="[1349,1452,1850,1876]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">KUMCC</collectionCode>
21-0468 is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFE15F8B27AA2536D" authority="ARSEF 1040" authorityName="ARSEF" authorityYear="1040" box="[460,748,1886,1912]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFE15F8B27A01536D" box="[460,591,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">B. bassiana</emphasis>
ARSEF 1040
</taxonomicName>
with high statistical supports (
<figureCitation id="1361E7CA101FFFAAFB9AF8B37CE8536D" box="[1091,1190,1886,1912]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1709,1731]" captionTargetBox="[332,1281,195,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[298,1289,190,1685]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Phylogram generated from maximum likelihood analysis based on a combined ITS, rpb1, rpb2, tef1-α and Bloc sequence datasets. Related sequences were taken from Chen et al. (2018) and Khonsanit et al. (2020). A total of 81 strains are included in the combined gene analyses; 5090 total characters including gaps (ITS: 1–566 bp, rpb1: 567–1307 bp, rpb2: 1308–2430 bp, tef1-α: 2431–3429 bp, Bloc: 3430-5090 bp). Tree topology of the ML analysis was similar to the BI. The matrix had distinct alignment patterns, with the final ML optimization likelihood value of -29154.321884 (ln). All free model parameters were estimated using the RAxML model, with 1867 distinct alignment patterns and 15.05% of undetermined characters or gaps. Estimated base frequencies were as follows: A = 0.242248, C = 0.283924, G = 0.257262, T = 0.216566, with substitution rates AC = 0.928484, AG = 3.845624, AT = 0.649405, CG = 0.874887, CT = 4.792288, GT = 1.000000. The gamma distribution shape parameter alpha = 0.712530 and the Tree-Length = 1.618181. The final average standard deviation of split frequencies at the end of total MCMC generations calculated as 0.009746 in BI analysis. The species determined in this study are indicated in red.Bootstrap values equal to or greater than 70% (ML, left) and Bayesian posterior probabilities (BI, right) equal to or greater than 0.95 are given at the nodes. Hyphens (-) represent support values less than 70% in ML/0.95 in BI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520359/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Figure 4</figureCitation>
). Therefore, our isolate 
<collectionCode id="ED4B638A101FFFAAFF51F86F78A15389" box="[136,239,1922,1948]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">KUMCC</collectionCode>
21-0468 is identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC101FFFAAFE26F86E7A925389" authorityName="ARSEF" authorityYear="1040" box="[511,732,1922,1948]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis id="B92E275D101FFFAAFE26F86E7A925389" box="[511,732,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Beauveria bassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a new host record based on morphological features and phylogenetic evidences.
</paragraph>
